			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2008</a> paper:</span><br><i>A Practical Evaluation of Using TXL for Model Transformation</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/HongzhiLiang.html">Hongzhi Liang</a>, <a href="../profile/JürgenDingel.html">Jürgen Dingel</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_16">10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_16</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagM">T5E: Empirical Evaluation</span></a><ul><li> It is explicitly an evaluation of using TXL for model transformation, focusing on practical evidence and assessment.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> TXL is used for performing transformations, so model-to-model / source-to-source transformation is central.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3b.html"><span class="tagL">T3B: Transformation Languages</span></a><ul><li> The work assesses a specific transformation-language technology (TXL) in the model-transformation setting.
</li></ul></li></ul>
